Welcome to gsports

Run "rake doc:app" to generate API documentation for your models, controllers, helpers, and libraries.

Requirements:
  - ImageMagick
  - RAILS VERSION 2.1
  - MySql 5
 
Required Gems:  
      rmagick
      hpricot
      htmlentities
      rake 0.8.1
      haml
      mime-types
      httpclient
      mysql
      stomp
      mocha (for tests)
      RedCloth >= 3.301 "sudo gem install RedCloth --source=http://code.whytheluckystiff.net"

      You might be able to use "sudo rake gems:install" to get all of these

Required Plugins:      
    - exception-notification:
      script/plugin install http://dev.rubyonrails.org/svn/rails/plugins/exception_notification/

    - The engines plugin for Rails 2.1:
      script/plugin install http://railsengines.org/news/2008/06/01/engines-2-1-0-release/

    - Community engine:
      git clone --depth 1 git://github.com/bborn/communityengine.git vendor/plugins/community_engine

     - ActiveMessaging:
       script/plugin install http://activemessaging.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/plugins/activemessaging

Other:

   - Active MQ must be installed and running
     for the background video upload and checking
     http://activemq.apache.com/
  - Memcached would be a good idea too, it is used by CE when available
